  "market_context": "NQ had already rallied with multiple consecutive expansion candles into a significant higher time frame swing high, sweeping prior highs on the daily chart. A continuation setup formed on the 1-hour but appeared late in the expansion phase.",
  "key_observation": "The continuation failed hard because price had already delivered three expansion candles and reached a significant HTF objective, exhausting the move and transitioning into a new phase of price.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Observed that the continuation setup on the 1-hour chart failed sharply rather than extending higher.",
    "Step 2: Zoomed out to the higher time frame and saw that NQ had just swept all the previous highs on the daily.",
    "Step 3: Counted multiple (1-2-3) expansion candles preceding the setup, signalling the move was already mature.",
    "Step 4: Concluded that taking longs after HTF objectives are met and after multiple expansion candles is where traders get trapped in a new phase of price."
  ],
  "outcome": "Continuation failed; price reversed sharply after the setup",
  "lessons": "Avoid taking continuation entries after price has already produced multiple expansion candles and reached a significant higher time frame objective. These are exhaustion zones where reversals begin, not continuations.",
